  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Breakfasts For Primary School Children: A Feasibility Study</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children in Tanzania suffer from high levels of poverty, malnutrition and poor health. Hunger is common, making it difficult for children to attend school and perform well. Girls are particularly affected &#x2013; their enrolment in school is lower than boys, their drop-out rates higher and their performance worse. This research will gather evidence from a breakfast feeding programme which feeds 984 children in 3 primary schools every day and which has so far increased their attendance by 28%. Much of the food eaten by the children is grown in the schools, reducing the costs of feeding them. By providing these children with a nutritious breakfast every day, children are performing better because they are no longer hungry. This research project will result in a fully costed proposal for extending the feeding programme to another 25 primary schools in the region, which would mean that 16,700 children could learn better, free from hunger.</narrative>
  </description>
